{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce a legal maximum class size of 24 pupils in primary schools in England",
        "additional_details": "Average primary classes in England are 26\u201327 pupils, with no legal limit for Years 3\u20136. Nearly 1 in 5 pupils have SEND. Smaller classes would improve learning, behaviour, and wellbeing, reduce teacher workload, increase teacher retention, and make inclusive classrooms possible. There are other countries with smaller classes which have better outcomes.",
        "background": "Pass legislation to limit all primary school classes in England to 24 pupils. This would help ensure teachers can manage classrooms effectively, that pupils get the support they need, and that inclusive practice for SEND children is realistic",
